AVIAN INFLUENZA (48): AFRICA (SUB-SAHARAN) SITUATION UPDATE, FAO
****************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Wed 9 Oct 2019
Source: Sub-Saharan Africa HPAI situation update, FAO Animal Health Service/EMPRES [abridged, edited]
https://tinyurl.com/yyr9czgz


a. Overview
1. Situation: Highly pathogenic avian influenza virus (H5N1 and H5N8 subtypes) with pandemic potential in countries of sub-Saharan Africa since February 2017.
1.1. Confirmed countries (H5N1): Burkina Faso, Cameroon, Cote d'Ivoire, Ghana, Niger, Nigeria, and Togo.
1.2. Confirmed countries (H5N8): Cameroon, Democratic Republic of the Congo, Namibia*, Niger, Nigeria*, South Africa*, Uganda, and Zimbabwe.
1.3. Animal/environmental findings: Please see reports from individual countries below. No new reports since the previous update (11 Sep 2019).
1.4. Number of human cases: None reported to date.
* Countries reporting cases in the current wave (since 1 Oct 2018)

Map 1. Officially reported HPAI outbreaks (H5N1 and H5N8 subtypes) in sub-Saharan Africa, by onset date (1 Oct 2017-9 Oct 2019) [to view, please go to the source URL]
Map 1A. Domestic and wild since start of the current wave (1 Oct 2018).
Map 1B. Domestic/wild/captive from 1 Oct 2017-30 Sep 2018

b. Situation update
No new events reported since the last update (11 Sep 2019).

Table 1. Summary of countries affected during current wave (start 1 Oct 2018), but no new H5N8 HPAI events reported since last update (11 Sep 2019) [https://tinyurl.com/y2xx7rje]

Country / 1st admin region / Date of last outbreak / Number of reported outbreaks, current wave
Namibia / Karas / 20 Jun 2019 / 5
Nigeria / Bauchi, Edo, Plateau / 21 Apr 2019 / 7
South Africa / Eastern Cape, Free State, Northern Cape, Western Cape / 1 Jul 2019 / 10

[For a summary of H5N1 and H5N8 HPAI events reported in sub-Saharan African countries before the current wave (i.e., before 1 Oct 2018), see the 10 Oct 2018 situation update at http://www.fao.org/ag/againfo/programmes/en/empres/HPAI_Africa/2018/situation_update_2018_10_10.html. - Mod.AS]

