[The above update includes the mentioned useful maps and information on FAO's support to countries on the global and national levels (at the source URL).

For the locations of HPAI events/infections in non-poultry, including wild birds in Africa since 1 Oct 2018, please refer to OIE's interactive map at https://tinyurl.com/y65mmn4j (click on the cluster, zoom in).

A recent paper (ref. 1) emphasizes the need for more extensive surveillance studies to determine the South African avian influenza gene pool and relevant local host species.
Reference
---------
1. Poen MJ, Fouchier RAM, Webby RJ et al: Evidence of the presence of low pathogenic avian influenza A viruses in wild waterfowl in 2018 in South Africa. Pathogens. 2019; 8(4): 163; https://www.mdpi.com/2076-0817/8/4/163. - Mod.AS

